    "Optimal Feature Selection for Splitting: At each tree node, the algorithm pinpoints the most effective feature for data division.",
    "It does so by evaluating diverse split criteria, such as Gini impurity for classifications or mean squared error for regressions.",
    "Data Splitting:With the chosen feature in hand, the data segregates into subsets grounded in potential feature values.",
    "Repetition of the Process:The splitting course repeats for each subset, sculpting new tree branches.",
    "This recursive sequence endures until meeting the stopping criterion."
